This code implements training a neural network model for classifying human activity from sensory data. It uses the PyTorch library to build the deep network, pandas to work with CSV files, and argparse to configure parameters via the command line. The program loads training and test data, builds a multilayer perceptron with regularization (batch normalization and dropout), and saves the predictions to a file for later use.

Training data with features and class labels is loaded from the CSV file 'trainYX.csv', test data without labels is loaded from 'testX.csv', and the prediction results are saved to the file "HAR_baseline.csv."

